Mocked modules
If your component depends on modules that are imported into the component file, you can mock those modules to control and assert on their behavior This is detailed in the mocking modules guide You can then import the mocked module (which has all of the helpful methods of a Vitest mocked function) into your story and use it to assert on the behavior of your component:
NoteUI stories

interactions nested in a collapsible group: Mocked modules If your component depends on modules that are imported into the component file, you can mock those modules to control and assert on their behavior This is detailed in the mocking modules guide You can then import the mocked module (which has all of the helpful methods of a Vitest mocked function) into your story and use it to assert on the behavior of your component: NoteUI storiestsTypescript// Replace your-framework with svelte-vite or sveltekit
